&lt;h1 id="flag-2--unauthorized-access">Flag 2 : Unauthorized Access
&lt;/h1>&lt;p>When I created the first page , I noticed it was assigned an id of 6&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://amca-qt.github.io/p/micro-cms-v1-writeup/img/2.PNG"
width="775"
height="371"
srcset="https://amca-qt.github.io/p/micro-cms-v1-writeup/img/2_hu4653122158811886795.PNG 480w, https://amca-qt.github.io/p/micro-cms-v1-writeup/img/2_hu12053154240974720234.PNG 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="3"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="208"
data-flex-basis="501px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>When I visit the two pages provided before, I noticed that the pages have an id of 1 and 2. which means there must be another pages with a different id. So I go around by changing the &lt;code>id&lt;/code> from &lt;code>1&lt;/code> to &lt;code>10&lt;/code> but found nothing.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So I try explore everything on the web and found that the &lt;code>edit page also have id &lt;/code>&lt;/p>
